## Editing this clone — template-owned vs clone-owned

This repo is a **stamped clone of `cs-kernel`**. The files below are **generated
from the kernel template** (`cs-kernel/cs/templates/project/…`) and re-rendered by
`cs update` — **edit them in the kernel template, never here**, or the change
drifts and is overwritten on the next update:

- `CLAUDE.md`, `README.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/projects/README.md`
- `.claude/settings.json`, `.claude/skills/*`, `.claude/commands/*`
- `bin/cs_operator_cron.sh`, `.env.example`, `.gitignore`, `requirements.txt`

**Clone-owned — edit freely here:**

- `manifest.toml` — the declared per-company variance (the ONE place values change)
- `company/*.md` — prose slots: the *file* is templated, its **content is yours** to author for this company
- `campaigns/<name>/` — campaign pack content
- `docs/projects/<name>/` — per-project working folders (dossiers, plans, working files)
- `.env`, `ext/`

Rule of thumb: **behavior/shape → kernel template; company data → clone.** A change
that would help every clone belongs in `cs-kernel` (rule of two + anti-fork charter).

## 0. Operator profile

Mario — founder. Wants this to run by itself **once trusted**: prepare the
day's mail in the right voice, review, send, let replies return to
{{ email_address }}. Course corrections are cheap; an unwanted blast — or a
tone-deaf mail to someone we already talk to — is not.

## 1. The engine daemon (the body)

On `desktop.mrcall.ai` a dedicated user `mrcalld` runs one engine per profile
as systemd units `zylch-server@<uid>`, each on a unix socket
`/run/mrcalld/<uid>.sock`, fronted by Caddy at `{{ engine_ws_url }}/ws/<uid>`.
The {{ email_address }} profile is `{{ engine_owner_uid }}`
(config `CS_ENGINE_OWNER_UID`).

Auth chain (headless): the cs service-account key signs a Firebase **custom
token** locally (`cs/auth.py`), exchanged for an **ID token** (~1h, cached at
`~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/id_token.json`); the WS handshake carries it as
`Authorization: Bearer` and the daemon gates `token.sub == OWNER_ID`. We never
bypass that gate.

**Outreach/reply policy lives in the profile, not this repo.** The declared-AI
identity (if any), signature, recipient-language rule and the LLM-ism ban list
are in `USER_NOTES` of the {{ email_address }} profile — read/edit via the
engine's own `settings.get` / `settings.update` RPC, never via ad-hoc prompt
files. **`USER_NOTES` is the biggest per-company artifact.**

**RPC response shapes — the wrapper key is NOT uniform (wrong key → 0 rows):**
`emails.search`/`list_inbox`/`list_sent` → `{"threads":[…]}`;
`emails.list_by_thread` → `{"emails":[…]}` (note: `emails`, not `threads`);
`tasks.list`/`campaign.list`/`campaign.contacts`/`drafts.list` → a bare array
(other `campaign.*` writes — `create`/`add_contact`/`update_contact` — return
a dict, not an array; don't assume the wildcard covers them, corrected
2026-07-14 doc-critic pass);
`settings.get` → `{"values":{…}}`; `account.who_am_i` → `{signed_in,uid,email,…}`.

> Company-specific engine/API access (e.g. the mrcall-agent configurator) lives in [company/claude-extra.md](company/claude-extra.md).

## 2. CLI verbs (thin transport)

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m cs <verb>
```

`plan` (producer worklist) · `whoami` · `rpc <method> ['{json}']` ·
`thread <email>` · `contacted <email>` (dedup truth = Gmail Sent) · `tasks` ·
`business <email>` ({% if crm_adapter == 'shopify' %}Shopify Admin GraphQL{% elif crm_adapter == 'starchat' %}StarChat CRM{% else %}CRM{% endif %}) ·
`dossier <email>` (thread + contacted + tasks + CRM + verdict) ·
`ask "<q>"` (read-only engine query) · `draft-reply "<msg>"` (**DRAFT only**,
send-incapable) · `review` · `drive ls|search|cat` (read-only — no write
method exists; only `search`'s default path is code-scoped to `{{ drive_scope }}`, `ls`/`cat`
have no code-level scope filter and rely on what's actually shared with the
service account, corrected 2026-07-14 doc-critic pass) ·
`campaign list|pending|reconcile|mark|queue-draft|send-draft` ·
`campaign packs|send-reminder|send-sms` (fixed-template lifecycle) ·
`chat "<msg>" [--allow …]` (supervised SEND path — DENIED to the headless
operator) · `accounts` · `cron install|uninstall|status` (manage the
operator's own crontab entry) · `--account <name>`.

## 3. Pipeline (one daily run)

1. **Worklist** — `cs plan`{% if producer_adapter == 'none' %} (reply-only — no producer wired; empty worklist){% else %}: ingest the `{{ producer_adapter }}` producer, self-filter (`SELF_UIDS`/`SELF_EMAILS`), suppression{% endif %}.
2. **Dossier — MANDATORY before any contact** — `cs dossier <email>`: threads,
   recent-contact check, tasks, CRM. Dedup truth is Gmail's own Sent folder
   (`cs contacted` via `cs/gmail_archive.py`), NOT the engine archive.
3. **Decide**: thread exists → reply in it; prior relationship → informed
   outreach; genuinely cold → cold template, flagged; contacted within
   `DEDUP_DAYS` / suppressed / self → **stop**.
4. **Draft via the engine** (`cs draft-reply` / `cs chat "componi …"`) — never
   from scratch in cs.
5. **Review** (desktop app or Gmail Drafts). 6. **Send** — only through the
   engine's approval gate (`cs chat … --allow send_draft`), after review.
7. **Replies** land in {{ email_address }}, re-ingested as tasks.

